        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/35/45",
        "text": [
          "٣٥. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): مَنْ أَسْرَعَ إِلَى النَّاسِ بِمَا يَكْرَهُونَ، قَالُوا فِيهِ بِمَا لَا يَعْلَمُونَ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "35. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: If someone is quick in saying about people what they dislike, they speak about him that about which they have no knowledge."
          ]
        }
      }
